	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65302157"><p>We have always used version control. For whatever reason, Git became the dominant platform. Nearly everyone in software development uses it, whether or not they have anything to do with Linux. That's why it's so famous.

</p><p>A historical perspective might be interesting. It's really not clear why Git "won". Mercurial also offers distributed repositories, is OSS, and was first released at the right time. Why did Linus decide to "roll his own".</p></div>
	</div>

